<main id="main" class="container narrow">
  <%- include('../partials/flash') %>
  <p class="eyebrow">Security architecture</p>
  <h1>Security &amp; Trust</h1>
  <p class="lead">USF Capital clearly separates real application protections from illustrative capital-market messaging used only to make the demo feel like a polished investor portal.</p>

  <h2>Real protections built into this app</h2>
  <ul class="check-list">
    <li>Passwords are hashed with bcrypt, so the app never stores a plain-text password.</li>
    <li>Optional two-factor authentication uses authenticator-app codes with QR setup.</li>
    <li>Every state-changing form is protected by a CSRF token.</li>
    <li>Login, registration, 2FA and money-moving routes have rate limits.</li>
    <li>Helmet sets a strict Content Security Policy, blocks framing, and limits browser capabilities.</li>
    <li>Request IDs are attached to responses to make debugging and review cleaner.</li>
    <li>Sensitive authenticated pages use no-store cache headers.</li>
    <li>Proxy trust is explicit for trusted deployments instead of being enabled everywhere.</li>
    <li>Session cookies are HTTP-only, same-site, secure in production, and backed by a SQLite session store.</li>
    <li>Users can review and revoke active sessions and inspect security-relevant account activity.</li>
    <li>Database calls use parameterized statements.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Demo risk model</h2>
  <div class="strategy-grid">
    <article class="strategy-card">
      <span class="strategy-number">01</span>
      <h3>Identity gate</h3>
      <p>Registration, login, demo KYC and optional 2FA demonstrate the account-protection journey.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="strategy-card">
      <span class="strategy-number">02</span>
      <h3>Money-flow guardrails</h3>
      <p>Deposits, withdrawals and allocation routes are rate-limited and protected by CSRF checks.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="strategy-card">
      <span class="strategy-number">03</span>
      <h3>Browser containment</h3>
      <p>Security headers reduce framing, unexpected resource loading and unnecessary device API access.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="strategy-card">
      <span class="strategy-number">04</span>
      <h3>Audit visibility</h3>
      <p>Account activity and active sessions make the demo feel operational, not decorative.</p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <h2>Illustrative messaging, not real claims</h2>
  <p>The badges and capital-desk language help the app feel premium, but they do not turn this project into a financial institution.</p>
  <ul class="check-list muted-list">
    <li>"Bank-grade" wording is illustrative. This is a software demo, not a bank.</li>
    <li>"Market desk" language refers to simulated UI behavior, not real trading operations.</li>
    <li>"Portfolio growth" numbers are generated by the simulation engine and are not investment performance.</li>
    <li>USF Capital is not registered with or regulated by any financial authority.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="callout">
    <p>USF Capital does not custody funds, process real payments, execute trades, provide advice, or offer investment products. Every displayed balance, price, return and position is simulated.</p>
  </div>
</main>
